Measurements — Body length 180 (
holotype
), 196 – 200 (mean 198, two 
paratypes
); body width 90 (
holotype
), 94 – 98 (mean 96, two 
paratypes
).

Prodorsum — (
Figure 4A, C
; 
Figure 5A
). Rostrum rounded. Costular lines short and thin. Lateral striae long. Interbothridial region with one pair of small median tubercles and two pairs of muscle sigilla. Postbothridial region with one pair of tubercles directed towards dorsosejugal suture. Rostral setae 10 – 14, setiform, slightly barbed (barbs visible only under high magnification). Lamellar and exobothridial setae (both 8) setiform, smooth. Interlamellar setae minute (1 – 2). Sensillus 53 – 61, setiform, thickened, curved, with barbs unilaterally.
